---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About - Seoul Sillok">
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-zinc-900 text-white flex flex-col items-center justify-center p-8">
    <div class="max-w-2xl w-full space-y-8 text-center md:text-left">
      <nav class="mb-12">
        <a href="/" class="text-gray-400 hover:text-white transition-colors">← Back to Map</a>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-6xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-8">Seoul Sillok</h1>

      <div class="space-y-6 text-lg text-gray-300 leading-relaxed font-light">
        <p>
          Seoul Sillok is a digital archive project that documents the administrative neighborhoods (Dong) of Seoul.
        </p>
        <p>
          Inspired by the Veritable Records of the Joseon Dynasty (Joseon Wangjo Sillok), this project aims to record the living history of the city through its smallest administrative units.
        </p>
        <p>
          The interactive map visualizes the 424 administrative dongs, merged and simplified to represent the organic communities they form. Each dong carries its own color based on its district (Gu), creating a mosaic of Seoul's diverse identity.
        </p>
        <p>
          This platform serves as a portal to explore these neighborhoods through visual records and stories.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="pt-12 border-t border-zinc-800 mt-12">
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">
          © {new Date().getFullYear()} Seoul Sillok. All rights reserved.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
